
SQL COUNT(),AVG() AND SUM() Functions

The COUNT() function returns the number of rows that matches a specified criterion

SELECT COUNT(colum_name)
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

The AVG() function returns the average value of a numeric column

SELECT AVG(column_name)
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

The SUM() function returns the total sum of a numeric column

SELECT SUM(column_name)
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

——EXAMPLE COUNT()——-

Find the number of products

SELECT COUNT(ProductID)
FROM Products;

——-EXAMPLE AVG()———
Find the average price of all products
SELECT AVG(Price)
FROM Products;

——-EXAMPLE SUM()——-

SLECT SUM(Quantity)
FROM OrderDetails


EXERCISE 1
Return the number of records that have price value set to 19

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM Products
WHERE Price =18;

Exercise 2

Use SQL function to calculate the average price of all products
SELECT AVG(PRICE)
FROM Products

Exercise 3
Calculate the sum of all the price column values in the products table

SELECT SUM(Price)
FROM Products